fm: bool searchMatrix(vector<vector<int>>& matrix, int target) {         if (matrix.empty() || matrix[0].empty()) return false;         int m = matrix.size();         int n = matrix[0].size();                  int lo = 0, hi = m * n - 1;         while (lo <= hi) {             int mid = lo + (hi - lo) / 2;             if (matrix[mid / n][mid % n] < target) {                 lo = mid + 1;             } else if (matrix[mid / n][mid % n] > target) {                 hi = mid - 1;             } else {                 return true;             }         }         return false;     }

fc: class Solution { public:     ListNode* deleteDuplicates(ListNode* head) {         ListNode *pi = head;         while (pi && pi->next) {             if (pi->val == pi->next->val) {                 ListNode *del = pi->next;                 pi->next = pi->next->next;                 delete del;             } else {                 pi = pi->next;             }         }         return head;     } };

fm: ListNode* partition(ListNode* head, int x) {         ListNode fake1(0), fake2(0);         fake1.next = head;                  ListNode *pi = &fake1, *pj = &fake2;         while (head) {             if (head->val < x) {                 pi->next = head;                 pi = head;             } else {                 pj->next = head;                 pj = head;             }             head = head->next;         }         pi->next = fake2.next;         pj->next = NULL;         return fake1.next;     }

fm: void merge(vector<int>& nums1, int m, vector<int>& nums2, int n) {         int i = m - 1, j = n - 1, k = m + n - 1;         while (i >= 0 && j >= 0) {             nums1[k--] = nums1[i] > nums2[j] ? nums1[i--] : nums2[j--];         }         while (j >= 0) {             nums1[k--] = nums2[j--];         }     }
